<DOC><DOCNO> AP880711-0166 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-11-88 2219EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Chile-Protest 1stLd-Writethru a0760 07-11 0217</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Chile-Protest, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0760,0220</SECOND><HEAD>About 200 Detained, 8 Injured In Anti-Government March</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: New grafs 1-3 UPDATE with 200 detained, more injured. Picksup 4th graf pvs, The march ...</NOTE><DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Riot police used tear gas and watercannons Monday night to scatter hundreds of anti-governmentdemonstrators who staged a ``March of Hunger'' to protest themilitary regime's economic policies.   Five buses were set afire, police said. A bus driver and afirefighter were badly burned and were hospitalized in seriouscondition, the official news agency Orbe said.   About 200 demonstrators were detained, Orbe reported. It saidone police officer and five demonstrators were injured, noneseriously.   The march was called by several communist-controlledorganizations of slum dwellers and joined by hundreds of otherdemonstrators, most of them students.   Police fought running skirmishes with the protesters for almostthree hours. Scattered groups of demonstrators were repatedlydispersed by police, but quickly regrouped at a differentintersection to resume their protest.   The demonstrators blocked traffic, sometimes with flamingbarricades, at a number of busy downtown intersections, asthousands of office workers returned home from work.   Earlier in the day, a dozen bombs went off at various points inthis capital city of 4.5 million people, causing damage but novictims, according to police.</TEXT></DOC>